2026-04-21 02:47:07 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 2 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 3 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 4 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 5 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 6 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 7 Switch Indicator LED', 'Control Module 8 Switch Indicator LED'] hypothesis_explanation='All control module indicator LEDs are physically missing from their holders, breaking the continuity of the circuit since the LEDs (and their series resistors) complete the series path for current flow. With all of these LEDs absent, the circuit remains open at each control module, so current cannot flow to energize the load. The power supply LED is on because it is in parallel to the supply and not in series with the rest; the lamp and indicator in the load module do not light up because they receive no power due to the breaks. The remaining circuit and cabling has been visually confirmed as correctly connected, and switches cannot conduct without the LED path present.'
